a Beloved Deaf Composer Appears to Be None of the Above\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_New_York_Times\" title=\"The New York Times\">The New York Times</a></i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2014-02-14</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+New+York+Times&amp;rft.atitle=In+Japan%2C+a+Beloved+Deaf+Composer+Appears+to+Be+None+of+the+Above&amp;rft.date=2014-02-06&amp;rft.aulast=Fackler&amp;rft.aufirst=Martin&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2014%2F02%2F07%2Farts%2Fmusic%2Frenowned-japanese-composer-mamoru-samuragochi-admits-fraud.html%3F_r%3D0&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATakashi+Niigaki\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Chayka, Kyle (2014-02-06). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://newsfeed.time.com/2014/02/06/deaf-japanese-composer-admits-hes-not-actually-deaf-didnt-write-his-own-music/\">\"<span style=\"padding-left:0.2em;\">\"</span>Deaf\" Japanese Composer Mamoru Samuragochi Admits He Had Ghostwriter &#124; TIME.com\"</a>. Newsfeed.time.com<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2014-02-10</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=%22Deaf%22+Japanese+Composer+Mamoru+Samuragochi+Admits+He+Had+Ghostwriter+%26%23124%3B+TIME.com&amp;rft.date=2014-02-06&amp;rft.aulast=Chayka&amp;rft.aufirst=Kyle&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fnewsfeed.time.com%2F2014%2F02%2F06%2Fdeaf-japanese-composer-admits-hes-not-actually-deaf-didnt-write-his-own-music%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATakashi+Niigaki\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:no